A British man has died in the Egyptian holiday resort of Sharm El-Sheikh.

The 50-year-old drowned while swimming off the Red Sea coast on Friday.

A British Foreign & Commonwealth Office spokesman said: 'We can confirm the death of a British national in Egypt on 22 February.

