'We are providing consular assistance to the family at this difficult time.'

Sharm el Sheikh is one of the main Red Sea resorts and attracts millions of tourists each year.

Several people drown there every year while snorkelling or swimming.

Last month a British catering company owner from Formby, Merseyside, died while singing karaoke on holiday at Sharm el-Sheikh.

Leah Rice, 41, was with her family at the five-star Hilton Sharks Hotel when she collapsed just one day before she was due to return home.

